name: dimensionless
description: a designation asserting the absence of an associated unit

name: candela
description:
SI base unit of luminous intensity (luminous power per unti solid angle emitted
    by a point light source in a particular direction)

name: nominalMinute
description: one minute of time excluding leap seconds, 60 seconds

name: nominalHour
description: one hour excluding leap seconds, 3600 seconds

name: nominalDay
description: one day excluding leap seconds, 86400 seconds

name: nominalWeek
description: one day excluding leap seconds, 604800 seconds

name: nominalYear
description: one year excluding leap seconds and leap days, 31536000 seconds

name: nominalLeapYear
description: one 366 day year excluding leap seconds, 31622400 seconds

name: tonne
description:
unit of mass equal to 1,000 kilograms, equivalent to approximately 2,204.6 
      pounds,1.102 short tons (US) or 0.984 long tons (imperial). 
      Not part of the SI, but accepted for use with SI units and prefixes

name: pound
description:
1 pound (symbol lb) in the Avoirdupois (commerce) scale, and defined 
      as exactly 0.45359237 kg. Also equal to 16 avoirdupois ounces and to 7,000 grains.

name: fahrenheit
description:
unit for temperature on the scale in which water freezes at 32 and boils 
      at 212 under standard conditions.

name: inch
description:
unit of length in the (British) imperial and United States systems 
      usually understood as 1/12 f a foot.

name: nauticalMile
description:
defined as exactly 1,852 meters (6,076.1 ft; 1.1508 mi). Historically, 
      defined as one minute of latitude.

name: Yard_Indian
description:
This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be
      accurate.

name: Link_Clarke
description:
This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be
      accurate.

name: Yard_Sears
description:
This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be
      accurate.

name: inchCubed
description: micromoles per square meter per second

name: radian
description: 2 pi radians comprise a unit circle.

name: grad
description: a plane angle equivalent to 1/400 of a full circle

name: steradian
description:
standard unit of solid angle measure, it is the solid angle which cuts out an area
      on a sphere that is the square of the sphere's radius; as a ratio of two areas, it has no
      dimension

name: hertz
description: derived unit of frequency in the SI, defined as one cycle per second

name: calorie
description:
unit of energy: amount of energy to raise the temperature of one gram of water 
      by one degree Celsius at a pressure of one atmosphere. cal = 4.1868 J

name: langley
description: unit of energy density = 41840 joule/m^2, = 1 calorie/cm^2

name: lumen
description:
SI unit for the total quantity of visible light in a defined beam or angle.
      1 lumen/m^2 = 1 lux. 1 lumen = 1 candela * steradian

name: lux
description: SI derived unit for illuminance, or luminous flux per unit area. 1 lx = 1 lm/m^2 = 1 cd * sr/m^2

name: becquerel
description:
SI derived unit of radioactivity. the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which 
      one nucleus decays per second, and equivalent to an inverse second, s^-1.

name: gray
description:
SI derived unit of ionizing radiation, defined as the absorption of one joule of 
      radiation energy per kilogram of matter (= 1 J/kg)

name: sievert
description:
SI derived unit of ionizing radiation dose (health effect of low levels of ionizing 
      radiation on humans). 1 Sv =  100 rem (rem is an older, non-SI unit)

name: katal
description:
derived SI unit for quantifying enzymatic activity.A property of the catalyst 
      (not rate of reaction), expressed in moles/second.

name: henry
description: SI derived unit for inductance; in SI base units: kg * m^2 * s^-2 * A^-2

name: megawatt
description: unit of power, to quantify rate of energy transfer. 1 W = J/s

name: kilowatt
description: unit of power, to quantify rate of energy transfer. 1 W = J/s

name: watt
description: unit of power, to quantify rate of energy transfer. 1 W = J/s

name: milliwatt
description: unit of power, to quantify rate of energy transfer. 1 W = J/s

name: megavolt
description:
Derived unit for electric potential, electric potential difference, 
      and electromotive force. 1 V = kg * m^2 * s^-3 * A^-1

name: kilovolt
description:
Derived unit for electric potential, electric potential difference, 
      and electromotive force. 1 V = kg * m^2 * s^-3 * A^-1

name: volt
description:
Derived unit for electric potential, electric potential difference, 
      and electromotive force. 1 V = kg * m^2 * s^-3 * A^-1

name: millivolt
description:
Derived unit for electric potential, electric potential difference, 
      and electromotive force. 1 V = kg * m^2 * s^-3 * A^-1

name: farad
description:
SI derived unit of electrical capacitance, the ability of a body to store an 
      electrical charge. 1 F = s^4 * A^2 *m^-2 * kg^-1

name: ohm
description:
an electrical resistance between two points of a conductor when a constant potential 
      difference of one volt, 
      applied to these points, produces in the conductor a current of one ampere

name: ohmMeter
description:
SI unit of electrical resistivity (fundamental property that quantifies how strongly a material 
      opposes the flow of electric current). reciprocal of electrical conductivity.

name: siemensPerMeter
description:
SI unit for conductivity, measure of a material's ability to conduct an 
      electric current.

name: siemensPerCentimeter
description:
SI unit for conductivity, measure of a material's ability to conduct an 
      electric current.

name: siemens
description:
SI derived unit of electric conductance, susceptance and admittance 
      (reciprocals of resistance, reactance, and impedance respectively). One siemens is equal 
      to the reciprocal of one ohm (and also called \mho\")"

name: weber
description: the SI unit of magnetic flux

name: tesla
description: unit for flux density. 1 tesla = 1 Wb/m^2 (one weber per square meter).

name: pascal
description: SI derived unit of pressure, 1 pascal = 1 newton/m^2

name: megapascal
description: SI derived unit of pressure, 1 pascal = 1 newton/m^2

name: kilopascal
description: SI derived unit of pressure, 1 pascal = 1 newton/m^2

name: hectopascal
description: SI derived unit of pressure, 1 pascal = 1 newton/m^2

name: atmosphere
description:
unit of pressure defined as 101325 Pa (1.01325 bar), sometimes used as a 
      reference or standard pressure

name: bar
description: non-SI unit for pressure (deprecated in some fields). 1 bar = 100000 Pa

name: millibar
description: non-SI unit for pressure (deprecated in some fields). 1 millibar = 1 hPa (100 Pa)

name: decibar
description:
non-SI unit for pressure. 1 decibar = .1 bar. Decibars are commonly used in aquatic 
      environments because 1 db is approximately equal to depth in meters.

name: tonnePerHectare
description: metric ton or tonne per hectare

name: milligramPerMilliliter
description: micromoles per square meter per second

name: milligramPerMeterCubedPerDay
description: milligram per cubic meter per day

name: acre
description: 1 acre = 4046.8564 square meters or 1 hectare = 2.4710 acres

name: bushelsPerAcre
description:
bushels per acre, 1 bushel = 35.23907 liters/1 acre = 4046.8564
      squareMeters

name: bushelPerAcre
description:
bushels per acre, 1 bushel = 35.23907 liters/1 acre = 4046.8564
      squareMeters

name: knot
description: unit of speed equal to one nautical mile per hour, exactly 1.852 km/hour

name: meterPerSecondSquared
description: micromoles per square meter per second

name: amperePerSquareMeter
description: ampere per meter squared, unit of current density

name: amperePerMeterSquared
description: amperes per square meter, unit of current density

name: molePerLiter
description: moles per liter (perferred over molarity, as molarity refers only to dissolved substances)

name: microequivalentPerLiter
description:
concentration of charge (on dissolved ions). conversions must know the name of the ion; 
      a single multiplier to SI is not possible

name: milliequivalentPerLiter
description:
concentration of charge (on dissolved ions). conversions must know the name of the ion; 
      a single multiplier to SI is not possible

name: equivalentPerLiter
description:
concentration of charge (on dissolved ions). conversions must know the name of the ion; 
      a single multiplier to SI is not possible

name: metersSquaredPerSecond
description:
meters squared per second, SI unit for kinematic viscosity, specific relative 
      angular momentum and thermal diffusivity. The unit may be better understood when phrased 
      as \meter per second times meter\" (velocity of an object with respect to a position)."

name: meterSquaredPerSecond
description:
meters squared per second, SI unit for kinematic viscosity, specific relative 
      angular momentum and thermal diffusivity. The unit may be better understood when phrased 
      as \meter per second times meter\" (velocity of an object with respect to a position)."

name: kilogramsPerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: kilograms per meter sqared per second

name: gramsPerCentimeterSquaredPerSecond
description: grams Per Centimeter Squared Per Second

name: gramsPerMeterSquaredPerYear
description: grams Per Meter Squared Per Year

name: kilogramsPerMeterSquaredPerYear
description: kilograms Per Meter Squared Per Year

name: gramPerCentimeterSquaredPerSecond
description: grams per square centimeter per second

name: gramPerDayPerHectare
description: grams Per Hectare Squared Per Day

name: gramPerMeterSquaredPerYear
description: grams per square meter per year

name: kilogramPerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: kilograms per square meter per second

name: kilogramPerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: kilograms per square meter per day

name: gramPerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: grams per square meter per day

name: milligramPerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: milligram per square meter per day

name: kilogramPerMeterSquaredPerYear
description: kilograms per square meter per year

name: numberPerMeterSquared
description: number per meter squared, e.g., for a population density.

name: percent
description: percent, one part per hundred parts. a decimal ratio multipled by 100

name: permil
description: permil, one part per thousand parts. a decimal ratio multipled by 1000

name: wattPerMeterSquared
description: watts per square meter, also, 1 kilogram per second cubed (ie, a flux)

name: wattPerMeterSquaredPerSteradian
description: watts per square meter, in a solid angle

name: microwattPerCentimeterSquaredPerSteradian
description: watts per square centimeter, in a solid angle

name: wattPerMeterSquaredPerNanometer
description: watts per square meter, per unit of wavelength

name: microwattPerCentimeterSquaredPerNanometer
description: watts per square centimeter, per unit of wavelength

name: wattPerMeterSquaredPerNanometerPerSteradian
description: watts per square meter, per unit of wavelength in a solid angle

name: microwattPerCentimeterSquaredPerNanometerPerSteradian
description: microwatts per square centimeter, per unit of wavelength, in a solid angle

name: molePerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: micromoles per square meter per second

name: micromolePerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: micromoles per square meter per second

name: micromolePerCentimeterSquaredPerSecond
description: micromoles per square centimeter per second

name: megajoulePerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: megajoules per square meter per day

name: langleyPerDay
description: Langley (Ly) per day. Ly is a unit of energy density = 41840 joule/m^2, = 1 calorie/cm^2
